channel.title: Compile Error, Please Help!
channel.description:
I received an error while compiling. Could you please help me?
Error: [IMG]http://img841.imageshack.us/img841/3205/cerror.png[/img]
Compiler Code: [CODE]@echo off cd ../src echo Compiling palidino76.rs2.io.packets "C:\Program Files\Java\jre6\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ../bin/ ./palidino76/rs2/io/packets/*.java pause[/CODE] OS: Windows 7

item.title: Compile Error, Please Help!
item.dc:creator: @Sanskrit Sanskrit
item.description:
@Sanskrit wrote:

TheSickSign:

Ohh, I didn’t say i can’t get Jdk. But, I know you can compile with Jre6, it’s possible, if you couldn’t compile with Jre6 it would be a whole lot different error…

No, you actually cannot compile with jre, it doesn’ t have the javac executable in its files. The only way you can use jre in a batch file for your server is for running your server client.
